-- European Stocks Rise as Data Shows Rebound in U.S. Capital Goods Demand
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-09-24T12:33:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/european-stocks-strengthen-after-orders-for-u-s-capital-equipment-rebound.html
European stocks advanced after a
report showed orders for U.S. capital equipment rebounded in
August, signaling a slowdown in business investment may be less
severe than some economists projected.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index gained 0.3 percent to 261.81 at
1:32 p.m. in London, after losing as much as 0.8 percent earlier
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  